<FIRST>r i PM-Bangladesh-Bus     06-10 0088</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Bangladesh-Bus,0090</SECOND>
<HEAD>30 Feared Killed When Bus Falls in River</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Navy divers recovered 15 bodies and
searched for 15 more believed trapped in a bus that fell into the
Daratona River while driving onto a ferry in southern Bangladesh,
police said today.
   The bus was carrying about 48 people Friday when it toppled into
the river near Bagerhat, 85 miles south of Dhaka, Bagerhat police
said. Eighteen people swam to safety, the authorities said.
   The bus was traveling from Perojpur to nearby Bagerhat.
</TEXT>
