<HEAD>Police Offer Reward for Capture of Convicts</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEAPOLIS, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Six of eight convicts who escaped from a
maximum security prison after killing two guards remained at large
Saturday and police announced a $300,000 reward for information
leading to their arrest.
   Two convicts, both Turkish Kurds, were captured Thursday just
hours after the eight inmates overpowered guards and shot their way
out of the prison on this south Aegean island.
   Police mounted a massive search of the region and the
northeastern Crete coastline for the remaining six _ four Greeks, a
Briton and a Tanzanian.
   A police official said a $300,000 reward was offered for
information leading to capture of the men, who were serving time for
robbery, drug trafficking and other convictions.
