<SECOND>AM-BRF--Near Collision,0173</SECOND>
<HEAD>Report: U.S. Jets Involved In Near Miss With Pan Am Jetliner</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HAMBURG, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two U.S. Air Force jet fighters
nearly collided with a Pan Am jumbo jet over West Germany, a
magazine reported on Saturday.
   The U.S. Air Force said it had received no reports of a near
collision.
   Der Spiegel magazine said the incident occurred near the city of
Koblenz on Tuesday. The magazine, citing unidentified aviation
control officials, said two U.S. Air Force F-111s changed course
without contacting air traffic controllers and headed on a collision
course with the Pan Am jet.
   The magazine did not say how close the jet fighters came to the
Pan Am plane.
   A woman who answered the telephone at Pan Am's airport offices in
Frankfurt said company officials were not available for comment.
   ``We have no record of near misses involving F-111s for the time
reported or the past week,'' said Maj. Bruce McFadden, a spokesman
for the U.S. Air Force's European Command in Ramstein.
