<SECOND>AM-PLO-US,0176</SECOND>
<HEAD>Arafat Regrets American Veto at U.N.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TUNIS, Tunisia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   PLO leader Yasser Arafat said Saturday he
regretted the Amerian veto of a U.N. Security Council resolution
condemning Israel's crackdown in the Israeli-occupied territories.
   ``We regret that the United States had to resort to a veto while
calling themselves the champions of liberty and human rights,''
Arafat said at a news conference, held 48 hours after the third
official U.S.-PLO meeting in the Tunisian capital.
   ``I ask the president and the American administration: what are
Palestinian human rights under the occupation?'' he said.
