measures when it is a question of rights of Palestinians under the
occupation and in other regions of the world,'' he added.
   The United States said the resolution was unbalanced because it
condemned Israel's crackdown in the territories while ignoring
violence by Palestinians. The vote Friday was 14-1, with only the
United States against. Britain, France and Canada voted for it.
