<HEAD>Trudeau Missing From Guest List for White House Lunch</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Some of the best-known editorial cartoonists
had lunch at the White House on Friday, but the guest list didn't
include Doonesbury's Garry Trudeau.
   Trudeau lampooned Bush frequently in last year's campaign. He
joked that Bush put his manhood in a blind trust and that he had a
secret twin brother, Skippy, who took care of the nasty side of
politics.
   Asked if the Doonesbury cartoonist was on the guest list for the
private lunch, White House spokesman Marlin Fitzwater replied,
``Garry, unfortunately, isn't going to make it this year.''
   Asked if Trudeau ever would be invited, Fitzwater quickly added,
``Not in my lifetime.''
   The cartoonists' lunch is an annual event that former President
Reagan started. Among the guests were Pat Oliphant, Tony Auth and
Jeff MacNelly.
