pay back a $1 million loan.
   The county commissioners appreciated the thought, even though
there's not much to show for it, Brueckmann said.
   ``I think it's kind of funny,'' said Commissioner John Pignatelli.
   The $1 million loan must be repaid at the end of June, with
$37,000 in interest, Brueckmann said.
   To pay the loan, the county will need some relief, perhaps
through an increase in excise taxes, Pignatelli said.
