<DATELINE>COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Labor Secretary Elizabeth Dole told
graduates of Ohio State University that the best jobs in the future
will go mostly to the college-educated.
   The nation's work force is far too poorly educated for employment
demands in the year 2000 and beyond, when more than half of the jobs
in the United States will require education above the high school
level, Mrs. Dole said at Friday's commencement.
   ``Most Americans ... don't enter the work world with a diploma
from Ohio State University in their hands. Far too many don't even
have a high school diploma in their hands, and many of those who
have ... can't even read it,'' she said.
   Mrs. Dole received an honorary doctor of laws degree from Ohio
State.
</TEXT>
